# Ops & Port Isolation

Follow `/srv/VPS_MULTI_PROJECT_GUIDELINE.md` + `/srv/scripts/PORT_REGISTRY.md`. Inabiya cheat-sheet: `Docs/PORTS.md`.

## Inabiya reserved ports (host loopback)

| Port | Process | Mode |
|---|---|---|
| `127.0.0.1:3001` | `inabiya-web` | Docker prod |
| `127.0.0.1:4001` | `inabiya-api` | Docker prod |
| `127.0.0.1:3101` | Next | `pnpm dev:web` only |
| `127.0.0.1:4101` | Nest | `pnpm dev:api` only |
| `127.0.0.1:5433` | Postgres | compose infra |
| `127.0.0.1:6381` | Redis | compose infra |

Health: `http://127.0.0.1:4001/api/v1/health` (prod) or `:4101` (dev). API has **no** useful page at `/`.

## Must

- Only `green-city-caddy` binds public `80` / `127.0.0.1:8443` — no second edge proxy.
- Thin `vps_edge`: public web/gateway only; Redis/DB/workers on private / `*_internal` nets.
- Before publishing any new host port → update `PORT_REGISTRY.md`; bind `127.0.0.1:` not `0.0.0.0`.
- If using shared `edunex-postgres`: dedicated DB + **non-superuser** role — not superuser `edunex` in `DATABASE_URL`.
- Caddy site files under `/srv/automation/deploy/caddy/sites.d/*.caddy`; upstream must share a Docker network with Caddy.

## Don't

- Run Docker prod **and** `pnpm dev` on the same 3001/4001 pair.
- Point Caddy at `localhost:PORT` for another project’s container.
- Flat shared LAN / revive ghost compose paths.
- Publish app ports on all interfaces.
